Improv comedy was such a massive part of Covy’s life. I knew it would be really tough and super emotional going to a show again after losing him. 

Since we are both huge Fubar Fans plus I’ve watched Covy shine many times on the Loose Moose Stage, “A very Terry Christmas” felt like the right show to face this part of my grief coaster. 
 
Thank you so much @giver_terry for remembering Covy and giving me one of the best hugs ever. That night’s show was more special than you’ll ever know. 

Improv will always be a way I can stay connected to him and I’ll continue to embrace that ❤️😇

📷: @idylwyld - you are so wonderful for snapping these special pics for me 🥰

It’s been 7 months since Covy’s suicide… with today being his birthday he would have turned 42. I’ve been so reluctant to post anything about him on social media because it feels like there’s nothing I could write that would even come close to describing how incredible he was, how hard he worked on his mental health or how devastating it was losing him and the life we shared together. 

I sit here with tears streaming down my face thinking back to those excruciatingly painful early days of grief when all I wanted to do was to follow him into the dark. I’ve been stuck on one of the worst roller coasters imaginable but thankfully I’ve had a massive amount of support and an amazing therapist helping me through. 

Missing him extra hard today and feeling grateful to be surrounded by family. We’ll tell stories, laugh, cry and eat Covy’s essential bday cake (a McCain deep & delicious vanilla). 

As this new year rolls in, I’ll continue to learn how to carry my grief, put the pieces of my heart back together and live this new life with him as my angel.❤️
Just a quick message of gratitude for all the love & support left on my post yesterday about Covy. I’m not able to reply right now but I see and feel it. Thank you all so much ❤️
Girls just wanna have SUN! ☀️🌴 A few fave pics from family vacay 🥰 @ashley.colberg #auntietime #rivieramayamexico #niecelove

A couple years before Covy died nature became a really important part of his life and self care routine. One of his favourite things to do was load his pockets full of birdseed and go feed the chickadees at Weasel head park. I used to find seeds all over the floor of my Mini Cooper 😆 This special tattoo is for him 🐦🐝❤️ HUGE THANKS to the ridiculously talented @ryangagnetattoo

I’ve got myself a boyfriend! Isn’t he cute!?!? 😍

He’s one of the sweetest humans I’ve ever known and has been so open-hearted and understanding with all the complexities that come with dating a widow.

Happy Valentine’s Day Ty! You are truly such a gem and I’m so grateful to have you in my life ❤️🥰

Got another super special tattoo done yesterday. This pineapple is based on a drawing done for me by my close friend’s sweet daughter Margaret. She drew it for me shortly after Covy died during the worst days of my grief. His little smile made me smile so I framed it and named him Jerry. I’d say good night/good morning to him and he kept me company while I was struggling to get used to sleeping without Covy beside me. Not only does this tattoo remind me of her adorable drawing but it’s also a symbol of ALL the help, support and love that was given to me during this horrendously terrible time.💛

Massive thanks to the ridiculously talented @ryangagnetattoo for turning Jerry into the cutest tattoo ever! 🍍
Wigged out with an awesome gang of ladies for @tarynjae88 ‘s b-day 🎂🥳 So happy I got to be part of your celebration Taryn! Love you tons 💛
That time I pulled off a cool shutter drag portrait of my rockstar @idylwyld 🎸🤘❤️ #offcameraflash #shutterdrag #canonr6

On May 30, 2022, my world was shattered when I lost my beloved partner, Covy, to suicide. The pain of that loss is something words could never truly capture and there are still moments that feel like it can’t even be real that he’s gone. 

Covy had an incredible ability to make people laugh, his love was boundless, and his talents were unmatched. He left behind an abundance of beautiful memories that I will forever hold close to my heart. 💖

Covy was not only funny, loving, and ridiculously talented… he was also a warrior who fought so hard to overcome his mental health struggles.

This year I’m participating in @cspyyc’s #RunforLife2023 a fundraiser to remember loved ones lost to suicide and raise awareness for suicide prevention. I want to continue the legacy of resilience and strength that Covy embodied and make a positive impact on the lives of others who are struggling. If you'd like to donate or learn more about Run for Life, please click the link in my bio. 🙏💛

#RunForLife #SuicidePrevention #SuicideAwareness #MentalHealthMatters

🎉🎂 Happiest of birthdays to my wonderful boyfriend 🥳🎈

Ty - You’re the absolute coolest guy I know. Your guitar skills make me swoon,🎸😍 Your sensitivity and sweetness touch my soul daily, and your thoughtfulness never ceases to amaze me. 

You came into my life when I needed it the most, helping me mend my broken heart after an unimaginable loss. Your unwavering support and understanding has meant the world to me, and I’m profoundly grateful for you.

While my love for Covy will never fade, you’ve shown me that there’s room in my heart for new beginnings and happiness. 💕🥰🍪 @idylwyld

Team shirt for this Saturday 🐝 I am SO SO grateful for all the donations that have come in this past week. We’ve now raised over $5000 for the Centre for Suicide Prevention in Covy’s Honour 🥹🙏🧡 link in bio if you’d like to donate or learn more about @cspyyc ‘s #runforlife2023

I am absolutely overwhelmed by the outpouring of donations for the #RunforLife2023 … truly a testament to how much Covy is loved and missed. ❤️ Our team Covy’s Bees raised over $6k which goes towards the vital work of the Centre for Suicide Prevention @cspyyc *link in bio 

Thank you all so very much, especially to the bees that walked with me today 💛🐝🥰

I was lucky enough to win a great giveaway from @whatsupalberta - an in home meal cooked by Chef Jeff of @expatasia.ca 

It all went down last night and WOW what an incredible experience!! Hands down one of the yummiest meals I’ve had in my life plus it’s pretty freaking cool watching such a talented chef work his magic in your own kitchen 👏 I know I’m gonna be dreaming about the tiger cauliflower and the coconut creme brûlée for a while 😋 

HIGHLY recommend checking this out for yourself or for a great gift idea. I was surprised by how reasonably priced it is to do. He even takes care of the dishes 👌

Special thanks to my mom for our spooky season table set up 💀🎃 and to @sofia_katherine for the video clips 💛 #yycgiveaway #giveawaywinner #yycfood #yycfoodie
